3.5.1 Theorem 1 For any square matrix A with real number entries, A + A′ is a symmetric matrix and A – A′ is a skew symmetric matrix. - 3
3.5.2 Theorem 2 Any square matrix can be expressed as the sum of a symmetric and a skew symmetric matrix. - 3
3.5.3 Theorem 3 (Uniqueness of inverse) Inverse of a square matrix, if it exists, is unique. - 3
3.5.4 Theorem 4 If A and B are invertible matrices of the same order, then (AB)–1 = B–1 A–1 - 3
3.5.5 If A and B are symmetric matrices, prove that AB – BA is a skew symmetric matrix. - 3
3.5.6 Show that the matrix B′AB is symmetric or skew symmetric according as A is symmetric or skew symmetric. - 3








